title: "tf_utils.py" missing in the installation of shap 0.34.0
body:
Hi,
I installed shap 0.34.0 version using the command "conda install -c conda-forge shap". I am using tensorflow 2.0.0 and found that tf_utils.py file was not present in /shap/explainers/ folder after installation.
I got this error as well 
e = shap.DeepExplainer(model, background)

Error:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
TypeError                                 Traceback (most recent call last)
<ipython-input-10-a172dc89d0f7> in <module>
      1 # explain predictions of the model on three images
----> 2 e = shap.DeepExplainer(model, background)

/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/shap/explainers/deep/__init__.py in __init__(self, model, data, session, learning_phase_flags)
     78 
     79         if framework == 'tensorflow':
---> 80             self.explainer = TFDeepExplainer(model, data, session, learning_phase_flags)
     81         elif framework == 'pytorch':
     82             self.explainer = PyTorchDeepExplainer(model, data)

/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/shap/explainers/deep/deep_tf.py in __init__(self, model, data, session, learning_phase_flags)
    147             if self.data[0].shape[0] > 5000:
    148                 warnings.warn("You have provided over 5k background samples! For better performance consider using smaller random sample.")
--> 149             self.expected_value = self.run(self.model_output, self.model_inputs, self.data).mean(0)
    150 
    151         # find all the operations in the graph between our inputs and outputs

/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/shap/explainers/deep/deep_tf.py in run(self, out, model_inputs, X)
    294         """ Runs the model while also setting the learning phase flags to False.
    295         """
--> 296         feed_dict = dict(zip(model_inputs, X))
    297         for t in self.learning_phase_flags:
    298             feed_dict[t] = False

/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/tensorflow_core/python/framework/ops.py in __hash__(self)
    711     if (Tensor._USE_EQUALITY and executing_eagerly_outside_functions() and
    712         (g is None or g._building_function)):  # pylint: disable=protected-access
--> 713       raise TypeError("Tensor is unhashable if Tensor equality is enabled. "
    714                       "Instead, use tensor.experimental_ref() as the key.")
    715     else:

TypeError: Tensor is unhashable if Tensor equality is enabled. Instead, use tensor.experimental_ref() as the key.
